org.jcvi.jillion.core.datastore

Class DataStoreFilters

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jcvi.jillion.core.datastore.DataStoreFilters

  • public final class DataStoreFilters
extends Object
    DataStoreFilters is a utility class that contains factory methods to create several different types of DataStoreFilter objects.
    Author:
    dkatzel

      • alwaysAccept

        public static DataStoreFilter alwaysAccept()
        Get a DataStoreFilter instance whose DataStoreFilter.accept(String) always returns true.
        Returns:
        a DataStoreFilter instance; never null. May return the same instance multiple times.

      • neverAccept

        public static DataStoreFilter neverAccept()
        Get a DataStoreFilter instance whose DataStoreFilter.accept(String) always returns false.
        Returns:
        a DataStoreFilter instance; never null. May return the same instance multiple times.

      • newIncludeFilter

        public static DataStoreFilter newIncludeFilter(Collection<String> ids)
        Create a new DataStoreFilter instance whose DataStoreFilter.accept(String) returns true if and only if the id is contained in the given collection of ids (and false otherwise).
        Parameters:
        ids - a collection of ids that should be accepted by the new DataStoreFilter; can not be null.
        Returns:
        a new instance; never null.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if ids is null.

      • newExcludeFilter

        public static DataStoreFilter newExcludeFilter(Collection<String> ids)
        Create a new DataStoreFilter instance whose DataStoreFilter.accept(String) returns false if and only if the id is contained in the given collection of ids (and true otherwise).
        Parameters:
        ids - a collection of ids that should be accepted by the new DataStoreFilter; can not be null.
        Returns:
        a new instance; never null.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if ids is null.

      • invertFilter

        public static DataStoreFilter invertFilter(DataStoreFilter filter)
        Create a new DataStoreFilter that wraps the given DataStoreFilter and returns the opposite value of the wrapped DataStoreFilter.
        Parameters:
        filter - the DataStoreFilter to invert; can not be null.
        Returns:
        a new DataStoreFilter that returns true if the wrapped filter's DataStoreFilter.accept(String) returns false and vice versa.

      • newMatchFilter

        public static DataStoreFilter newMatchFilter(Pattern pattern)
        Create a new DataStoreFilter instance whose DataStoreFilter.accept(String) returns true if and only if the id matches the given Pattern completely. The accept method of the returned filter should return identically values as returned by pattern.matcher(id).matches();.
        Parameters:
        pattern - a Pattern that will be used to match ids; can not be null.
        Returns:
        a new instance; never null.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if pattern is null.
        See Also:
        Matcher.matches()

      • containedInDataStore

        public static DataStoreFilter containedInDataStore(DataStore<?> datastore)
        Create a new DataStoreFilter that will only accept any ids that are contained in the given DataStore. The DataStore must remain open for the entire lifetime of this DataStoreFilter; otherwise it will be kept
        Implementation Note:
        internally the accept test is done using DataStore.contains(String).
        Parameters:
        datastore - the DataStore to check to see if the ids are contained in; can not be null.
        Returns:
        a new DataStoreFilter object; will never be null.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if datastore is null.
        Since:
        5.0
